asy FamilyWeasy won't return a video game to the Ducklings until he wins.VegesaursGinger the Tricarrotops explores the world of the crunchiest era, going on adventures throughout the colourful Vegesaur Valley.Spidey and His Amazing FriendsZola steals the Bookmobile along with the acclaimed the writer Millicent McKeen. The villains team up to steal back their old inventions from the museum's new exhibit.Octonauts: Above & BeyondThe Octonauts expand their exploration beyond the sea - and onto land. With new rides and new friends, they are prepared to protect any habitats and animals at risk on land or under the water.Stan CanButterflies on Stanley's solar panels mean he has no power for his vehicles or his Can-Bots.SupertatoEvil Pea wears a giant powersuit so powerful it knocks Supertato across the supermarket aisles. Carrot and Supertato plan to outsmart Evil Pea so she'll lose her new powers.Talking Tom Heroes: Suddenly SuperThe Heroes find themselves battling a rogue plant.Small PotatoesAnimated series about a group of potatoes who sing songs in different genres. Ruby sings a diva style ballad about the thing she loves more than anything else, school.Monster MakesIt is picnic day! Rebecca and Murphy craft a 'soup-er' fly in a bowl of soup. Meanwhile, on the Recycling Express, they transform an old storage tub into a terrific drum kit.Big Cook Little CookJen is doing the washing up, but her hands are going wrinkly. Gabby the goalkeeper visits the cafe, and the two chefs make a power shake to give her an energy boost for her next game of football.Let's Go for a WalkRanger Hamza and the Ramblers walk through town to water the flowers. On the way, they spot some horses, pretend to be ducks, look at colours in the sweet shop window and walk like signposts.BalamoryDr Ollie forgets who he asked to play the wizard in his play! Ava's memory-jogging machine helps him recall, but things get confusing at the nursery.Hey DuggeeEthel slips up and lands with a very big bump. Then